This set was optimized with mp3packer (remove some padding bits) and MP3val (correcting the MP3-file length reported by the MP3 header for proper seeking). Foobar2k was used to add ID3-tags, to avoid clipping by scaling the Global Gain to 89dB and to add ReplayGain tags. Final quality (TMB HQ): 266kbps 44.1kHz VBR stereo MP3. All MP3-players will play the file as usual. After all the optimizations, the MP3 file has been improved even more - a third (for normal stereo mp3-players invisible) channel with 17kbps 5.1 surround extension has been added with the MP3SX converter. Check the Fraunhofer explanations HERE. A software player for the MP3SX / MP3 Surround content can be found at all4mp3.com.
